g.text: UI Layer contains full separation of subdomains which can be grouped
into bounded contexts. Do not apply everything at once, as project will
evolve over time. After some time you will notice which subdomains
can be grouped. In process of building architecture you don't have to
provide all possible congurations - use what is needed .
Infrastructure here is grouped by it's solution in context of project. You
should provide necessary generic adapters as there can be many
providers for a specic solution. Solutions may group few functionalities
of a system ( Messaging for example ). Implement what is needed and
keep in mind that solutions and functionalities should be separated.
You should dene strict entry point for
domain mapper to create output contract
